		<section>
			<h2 id="presentation" tabindex="-1">Presentation</h2>
			<h3>How it works ?</h3>
			<p>The <code>function</code> add a tooltip accessible with keyboard, by using the tab key for every element pour tous les éléments passés en paramètre, possédant un <code>title</code>.</p>
			<h3>Démonstrations</h3>
			
			<div>
				<h4>Links</h4>
				<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit <a href="http://access42.net/MFP-lecteur-video-accessible.html" title="MFP accessible video player">MFP VideoPlayer</a></p>
				<p><a href="http://access42.net/MFP-lecteur-video-accessible.html" title="Title 2">Lien 2</a></p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-1-4">
				<h4>Abbreviation</h4>
				<p><abbr title="Web Content Accessibility Guidelines">WCAG</abbr></p>
			</div>
			
			<div class="col-1-4">
			<h4>Button</h4>
			<p><button type="button" title="A button with a title">click</button></p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-1-4">
			<h4>Image</h4>
			<p><img src="../img/access42.png" title="Digital Accessibility: Engineering, Consulting & Training " alt="Access42.net" /></p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-1-4">
			<h4>Input</h4>
			<form>
				<input type="text" title="an input, labelled with a title" />
			</form>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2 class="CTitre" id="imple" tabindex="-1">How to use it</h2>
			<p>Insert the code right before the closing <code>body</code>element of your HTML document. </p>
<pre>
<code class="html">&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="AccessTooltip.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</code>
</pre>
			<p>Create a CSS class for the tooltip (Beware : the "absolute" position is required) :</p>
<pre>
<code>Ctooltip{
	position:absolute;
	background-color:#FFFFF0;
	border:1px solid gray;
	border-radius:3px;
	padding:3px;
	box-shadow:2px 2px 2px #000;
	color:#000;
	font-size:80%;
}
</code>
</pre>
			<p>Then call the function right before the closing <code>body</code> element of your HTML document and use paramters to configure the tooltip : </p>
<pre>
<code class="javascript">&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;
AccessTooltip({
	objs : 'a, button, input, textarea, select',
	tooltipClassName : 'Ctooltip',
	toolTipBetween : 5,
	toolTipUp : false,
	mouse : true,
	tempDelay : 4000,
	useAriaDP : false,
	useEscClose : true
});
&lt;/script&gt;
</code>
</pre>	
		</section>
	</main>
</div>

</div>
<script type="text/javascript" src="../js/AccessTooltip.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
	AccessTooltip({
		objs : 'a, button, input, textarea, select, abbr, img',
		tooltipClassName : 'Ctooltip',
		toolTipBetween : 5,
		toolTipUp : false,
		mouse : true,
		tempDelay : 4000,
		useAriaDP : false,
		useEscClose : true
	});
</script>
